		description:
			"<p>Docflow is looking for a frontend hero to join our seasoned dev team and help us optimise our software in this document revolution.</p>\n<p>We help people to save time and deliver better documents. By innovating the creation, approval and publication of document flows, we are changing the document management software landscape for the education sector and beyond.</p>\n<p>Our document collaboration system OER Write enables people to systematically optimise their workflows and drastically improve on their team's efficiency. Founded in 2016, our customers include leading Dutch universities, such as The Amsterdam University of Applied Sciences, HAN, Inholland and Avans.</p>\n<p>What you'll do</p>\n<p>As a (Senior) Frontend Developer, you'll join the Development team that currently consists of four experienced Developers. You'll work both in a team and independently on making our software even better for our clients. Our frontend has been developed in React components, written in Typescript.</p>\n<p>In this role there is plenty of room for your ideas. Our team is growing a lot and we'll do our best to support your growth ambitions as much as possible. We're flexible, and as long as you're proactive and take responsibility of your own work, we'll be a great match!</p>\n<p>You</p>\n<ul>\n<li>have a getting-shit-done mentality;</li>\n<li>are extremely self-motivated;</li>\n<li>are able to work independently, also from home;</li>\n<li>have at least 3 years of experience with JavaScript - Typescript is a very big plus;</li>\n<li>and/or have experience with other frameworks, like React, Angular or Vue;</li>\n<li>have experience with HTTP/REST APIs;</li>\n<li>get bonus points if you have knowledge of any backend frameworks, preferably Ruby on Rails;</li>\n<li>have a good command of the English language;</li>\n<li>have a Dutch nationality and/or the right to work in the Netherlands without sponsorship (though remote is optional).</li>\n</ul>\n<p>What we offer you</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A sweet salary that's in conformity with the market;</li>\n<li>A team of talented developers that'll help you reach your ambitions;</li>\n<li>A unique, exciting position at a successful start-up with international ambition;</li>\n<li>Lots of freedom and responsibility in your role;</li>\n<li>Plenty of room for professional growth;</li>\n<li>Be part of a cross-functional and highly motivated team;</li>\n<li>A fun and informal working atmosphere;</li>\n<li>An Amsterdam Center office at TNW, with lots of events and other inspiring startups;</li>\n<li>Opportunity to work remotely - also after the COVID storm has passed.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>What we stand for</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Do it well or not at all;</li>\n<li>Keep it clear;</li>\n<li>Build solutions, not features;</li>\n<li>Explore, innovate, learn, repeat;</li>\n<li>Do all of the above with a great team.</li>\n</ul>\n",
