		description:
			"<p>Looking for new challenges while being part of a creative and inspirational team and on top you want to help making the world a better place? With our vision to not only offer the most sustainable and healthiest but also the most attractive beverage option we have developed a worldwide unique drinking system. What makes air up so special - we have managed to make water taste like apples or orange-passion fruit by only using scent. Completely without artificial additives or sugar and the best: you can even safe on plastic bottles as you can refill our bottle everywhere! Join us to establish the market segment of „scent based drinks“ as:</p>\n<p><strong>Webshop Frontend Developer (m/f/d) Shopify</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Your responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<ul>\n<li>You are responsible for the technical development (JavaScript, CSS, HTML, Liquid, Node.js, React) of our core sales channel: air-up.com</li>\n<li>You will drive our front- and back-end development of the web shop (currently running on Shopify, with a shift to a new platform plant in the next 18 months)</li>\n<li>Together with the Head of IT and the Head of e-commerce you drive the selection of the future shop platform</li>\n<li>You shape the core presence of air up (our web shop) and ensure we have reliable links &amp; interfaces to our supporting systems</li>\n<li>You have the capacity to structure your work according to modern agile development principles\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>That’s you:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Experienced in front-/ back-end development of shop websites and ideally also initial Shopify developer know how</li>\n<li>Good knowledge of JavaScript, CSS, HTML, Liquid, GIT, CI/CD</li>\n<li>Experience in Node.js, React, Next.js, GraphQL, REST APIs</li>\n<li>Python, PHP know-how, would be a plus</li>\n<li>An eye beyond the pure coding on the outcome of your product</li>\n<li>A sense of ownership for your development and the pride to continuously improve it</li>\n<li>A self-starter and self-organizer</li>\n<li>Fluency in English (min. B2)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>This is us:</strong></p>\n<p>We are much more than we are able to put into words - but to mention a couple of things which make working at air up great:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>We are a diverse team from all over the world that strives for greatness</li>\n<li>With us you will have a huge load of responsibility and a job that creates value and has impact in a short decision-making environment</li>\n<li>We value you bringing in new ideas and testing new concepts</li>\n<li>Our strong growth provides excellent development options - professionally as well as personally</li>\n<li>We support you with a yearly training budget and many internal training possibilities</li>\n<li>Free coffee, fruit and our own scent pods in the office are naturally also part of the deal</li>\n<li>Of course remote work works also! Without you missing out on anything (except for coffee and fruit ;-) )</li>\n<li>For balancing you benefit from a discounted Urban Sports Club membership and many other corporate discounts</li>\n<li>And last but not least - we never loose fun out of sight, neither in our day-to-day work nor at our regular team events</li>\n</ul>\n",
