			"<p>We’re looking for a DevOps Engineer to join the CPR team at our Tech Hub in Barcelona and build services in Golang and Kubernetes for 1000+ engineers.</p>\n<p>Our 30+ marketplaces have 1.5 billion visits per month across 3 continents, so the opportunity to have an impact is huge.</p>\n<h2><strong>Your day to day</strong></h2>\n<p>You’d be part of a team developing a state of the art scalable platform as a service solution for 30+ marketplaces, using Kubernetes, Docker and Microservices. Each marketplace brings its own infrastructure and a unique set of challenges, so no two days are ever the same.</p>\n<p>As well as automating the operations and production of large-scale distributed systems, you’d support features like blue-green deployments, automated canary releasing and automated promotion to production.</p>\n<p><strong>Your objective:</strong></p>\n<p>Support hundreds of instances and multi-tenant Kubernentes clusters for millions of consumers, and build self-service solutions for 1000+ developers!</p>\n<h2><strong>Working at Adevinta</strong></h2>\n<p>You’d be based in Barcelona, but would work closely with cross-functional, multicultural tech teams in Paris and around the world.</p>\n<p>Each team chooses their own tech stack and big data/cloud tools, and as teams are small everyone is involved in decision making. Because Adevinta is a new company - and we’re growing - there’s also a chance to influence the organisation’s engineering direction and decision-making processes.</p>\n<p><strong>Technologies and methodologies</strong></p>\n<p>Kubernetes, Golang, Docker, Microservices, Agile, CI/CD</p>\n<h2><strong>Interested?</strong></h2>\n<p>Please apply via the <a href=\"https://vonq.io/37ynruG\">'Apply' link</a>.</p>\n",
