		description:
			"<p>Quick Take: Axios is a growth-stage startup dedicated to providing trustworthy, award-winning news content in an audience-first format. We're hiring a Director of Engineering!</p>\n<p>Why it Matters: Delivering great products means great passionate and talented technologists. The Director of Engineering will set standards for Axios while growing, coaching, and holding accountable the staff that delivers our compelling products.</p>\n<p>The Details: Ideal candidates will embody an entrepreneurial spirit, a passion for Axios’ mission and will be responsible for the following:</p>\n<p>Work closely with Product, Design, and Engineering leadership to build a vision for technology at Axios\nPartner with Engineering Managers to set standards and define best practices\nHire, retain, support, and grow the engineering talent Axios needs to succeed\nCoach and mentor staff to help them grow in their abilities as they work with cross-functional product-oriented team members\nEnsure all engineers in your domain are delivering high-quality technical output\nOversee architectural process and help grow architectural skills across engineering\nPartner with engineers to plan, problem solve, and optimize for the best technical solutions\nDemonstrate excellent judgment in professional and technical decision making\nWeigh risk, maintainability, cost-impact, dev-impact, and business impact, to result in proposing the best possible solution\nPromote test-driven-development and prioritize strategies to reduce risk \nBe an authority on end-to-end systems architecture and modern pipeline design\nHold yourself and your team accountable to delivering high-quality, pragmatic results that meet the needs of the business in the timelines provided</p>\n<p>Qualifications:</p>\n<p>Proven track record with extensive experience as a software engineer, architect, and manager with deep, current technical experience \nExperience leading and managing multiple teams of developers in a fast-growth environment\nDeep, current technical capacity with software development, front-end architecture, data design and implementation, and enterprise-grade software delivery\nProven track record of creating pragmatic, maintainable systems, using industry-recognized best practices\nExperience shipping, maintaining, scaling, and evolving highly-utilized production products \nDeep experience applying agile practices to streamline team delivery and output\nSignificant, current knowledge of Python, Node related frameworks, and technologies\nExpertise in frontend technologies, specifically React and React Native\nExperience with Go or Native Mobile development, is a plus\nExtensive experience evaluating, implementing, and supporting third-party solutions for ad-tech, BI tooling, and general analytics a huge plus\nA passion for the Axios mission and media </p>\n<p>Don’t forget:</p>\n<p>Competitive salary\nHealth insurance (100% paid for individuals, 75% for families)\nPrimary caregiver 12-week paid leave\n401K\nGenerous vacation policy, plus company holidays\nCompany equity\nCommuter and cell phone benefit\nA commitment to an open, inclusive, and diverse work culture\nAnnual learning and development stipend</p>\n<p>Additional pandemic-related benefits:</p>\n<p>One mental health day per month\n$100 monthly work-from-home stipend\nTele-mental health services \nOneMedical membership, including tele-health services \nIncreased work flexibility for parents and caretakers \nAccess to the Axios “Family Fund”, which was created to allow employees to request financial support when facing financial hardship or emergencies \nWeekly company-sponsored exercise and meditation classes \nVirtual company-sponsored social events</p>\n",
